  
\title{ThMonoidalCategory}
\tag{theory}

 \p{Theory of *monoidal categories*}\p{To avoid associators and unitors, we assume that the monoidal category is *strict*. By the coherence theorem this involves no loss of generality, but we might add a theory for weak monoidal categories later.}
